A vibrant vintage 1960s travel poster style illustration depicting the Mumbai skyline at sunset, with iconic Art Deco buildings and the Gateway of India silhouetted against warm orange and pink skies. In the foreground, a confident speaker stands at a podium on an elevated stage, gesturing expressively toward a crowd of engaged professionals seated in rows. The scene is rendered with bold, flat colors, subtle grain texture, and geometric simplifications characteristic of mid-century advertising art. Decorative swooping lines and stylized clouds frame the composition, giving it an optimistic, aspirational energy. The color palette features deep teals, burnt oranges, golden yellows, and warm browns typical of vintage Indian tourism posters.
